summary:
The Security Council:
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Sierra Leone, 
Commending UNIOSIL's contribution to Sierra Leone's recovery, 
Extends UNIOSIL's mandate until 31 December 2007; 
Endorses increase in personnel to support elections; 
Calls for comprehensive assessment of UNIOSIL's role; 
Urges peaceful, transparent, free and fair 2007 elections; 
Emphasizes Government's primary responsibility for peacebuilding; 
Calls for continued support to Government; 
Encourages efforts to promote good governance. 
Welcomed report of secretary general and president of Sierra Leone 
 Stressing elections and UNIOSIL exit strategy 
 Welcomed progress in security sector reform 
 Welcomed Improved Governance and Accountability Pact 
 Reiterated appreciation for Special Court for Sierra Leone 
 Encouraged  Member States of the Mano River Union to continue dialogue 
 Calls upon all parties to demonstrate commitment to democratic process 
 Calls upon government to provide support for electoral institutions 
 Urges member states to provide technical and material support
The Security Council:

Calls on the Government of Sierra Leone to promote private sector development to generate wealth and employment opportunities, strengthen the judiciary, and promote human rights;

 Requests the Government to expedite implementation of Truth and Reconciliation Commission recommendations and calls on Member States to assist in funding the National Human Rights Commission;

Emphasizes the role of women in conflict prevention and resolution, and peacebuilding, and requests a gender perspective in implementing the UNIOSIL mandate, with adequate capacity, expertise, and resources;

 Requests the Secretary-General to report on progress on gender mainstreaming and the situation of women and girls, particularly protection from gender-based violence;

 Welcomes efforts to implement the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;

 Requests the Secretary-General to regularly inform the Council of progress made in implementing the UNIOSIL mandate;

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
